# Git Workflow Rule for Agents

**Never commit or push automatically.** Only commit when the user explicitly asks (e.g. "commit", "commit and push", "push it"). When in doubt, ask first.

Follow this workflow **before every push**. Do not skip steps.

## 1. Sync with main

- Before starting new work: `git checkout main && git pull origin main`
- Create your branch from the updated `main`
- If already on a feature branch, update it with the latest `origin/main` via rebase or merge before pushing; do not switch branches if that would disrupt uncommitted work

## 2. Create a branch with enforced naming

- **Allowed prefixes**: `feature/`, `fix/`, `chore/`, `docs/`, `refactor/`
- **Format**: `<prefix><kebab-case-description>` (e.g. `feature/hero-headline-rewrite`)
- **Max length**: 50 characters total
- **Avoid**: generic names like `feature/update`, `fix/fix`, `feature/changes`
- `git checkout -b <branch-name>`

## 3. Make changes

Implement the task on the branch.

## 4. Pre-commit checks (all must pass before committing)

Run from repo root:

- **Lint all projects**: `pnpm nx run-many -t lint` — zero errors
- **Typecheck**: run project configs explicitly — `npx tsc --noEmit -p apps/frontend/tsconfig.json` and `npx tsc --noEmit -p apps/backend/tsconfig.json` — zero errors
- **Secrets scan**: `git diff --cached --name-only` must **not** include `.env`, `credentials.json`, or paths matching `*secret*` (case-insensitive)
- **Debug artifacts**: search **staged** content for `console.log` and `debugger` — remove unless explicitly required; warn the user if any remain
- **Conflict markers**: search staged files for `<<<<<<<`, `=======`, `>>>>>>>` — **fail** if found

## 5. Commit

- Stage only intentional files — **never** commit `node_modules/`, `dist/`, `out-tsc/`, `.next/`, `out/`, `.angular/`, `.nx/cache/`, `__screenshots__/`, or Prisma migration files
- **Commit message**: clear summary line; add a body when the change needs context ("why")

## 6. Push and open a PR

- `git push -u origin HEAD`
- If **GitHub CLI** is available (`command -v gh` or `which gh`):
  - Create a PR with a **descriptive title**
  - **Body** must include:
    - **Summary** (bullet points)
    - **Changes** (files / areas affected)
    - **Test plan** (checkbox list)
- If `gh` is **not** available: push the branch only and tell the user to open a PR manually (include branch name and remote URL if known)

## 7. Post-push

- Print the **PR URL** when `gh pr create` succeeds
- If `gh` is available, run `gh pr checks` (or equivalent) and **report** CI status
- If checks fail, report **which** check failed and stop claiming the change is "green"
